      • getApplicationModule

        protected abstract EWTModule getApplicationModule()
        Must be implemented by subclasses to return the application module that creates and manages the user interface of this GEWT entry point. This method will only be invoked once. Therefore the implementation may create the module instance on the fly if it doesn't need to keep a reference to it.
        Returns:
        The application module
